Rectifier
This is one of a series of recent works using cloned houseplants and bluegrass grown in ad-hoc hydroponic systems. These plants are interspersed among plastic plants, begging the question, ‘Which is more natural, a plant reproduced from a mechanical mold or from a genetic blueprint?’
T29.1 2005
water, pumps, organic and synthetic plants, paper pulp, video and electronic equipment, plastic bins
60" x 144" x 72"
